Under those rules, states can receive an annual subsidence insurance grant of up to $3,000,000, awarded from the states share of the Abandoned Mine Land Fund.
In 2000, one $215,777 subsidence insurance grant was issued to Wyoming.
Through 2000, the Office of Surface Mining has granted a total of $11,779,058 to Colorado, Indiana, Kentucky, Ohio, West Virginia, and Wyoming for this purpose.
