Of the 247 potential emergencies referred to the Office of Surface Mining in 2000, 200 became emergency projects; 29 were determined to be not of an emergency nature, not related to coal mining, or were reclaimed by the landowner; and 18 were still under investigation on September 30, 2000.
Those projects which were not emergencies, but were otherwise eligible for reclamation, were referred to the states for consideration as high priority projects.
